# Commit And Push

When the user asks to "take a pull" from development, run exactly:

```bash
git pull origin development
```

- Do not add rebase, autostash, or other behavior-changing flags.
- Safe read-only/dry-run flags are acceptable when explicitly useful.
- For commit-and-push requests, commit all relevant current changes and push to
  `development` unless the user specifies a different branch.
- Do not use destructive git commands unless the user explicitly requests them.
